  "texts": [
    "It is exactly the multivariate Convolutional function's inverse.",
    "For example, giving input to the Convolutional layer and getting output then give the same output to deconvolutional layer can get you to the same input you given first.",
    "Deconvolution is just to reverse the input back to large size [73,74].",
    "Dilated Convolution (Atrous Convolution)A type of convolution by which the kernel inflates by inserting holes between the kernel elements.",
    "Another parameter to the Convolutional layers has been introduced by dilated convolution called the dilation rate."
  ]
